#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an3.156-162"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an3.156-162:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 3 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: paṭipadāvaggo (bj) | paṇṇāsakāsaṅgahitā suttantā (s1-3)
msgctxt "an3.156-162:0.2"
msgid "16. Acelakavagga "
msgstr "16. Naked "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an3.156-162:0.3"
msgid "156–162 "
msgstr "156–162 "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.295, sc1
msgctxt "an3.156-162:1.1"
msgid "“Tisso imā, bhikkhave, paṭipadā. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are three practices. "

msgctxt "an3.156-162:1.2"
msgid "Katamā tisso? "
msgstr "What three? "

# NOTE: Comm says: gāḷhā kakkhaḷā lobha-vasena thiragahaṇā
msgctxt "an3.156-162:1.3"
msgid "Āgāḷhā paṭipadā, nijjhāmā paṭipadā, majjhimā paṭipadā. "
msgstr "The addicted practice, the scorching practice, and the middle practice. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.156-162:1.4"
msgid "Katamā ca, bhikkhave, āgāḷhā paṭipadā? "
msgstr "And what’s the addicted practice? "

msgctxt "an3.156-162:1.5"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco evaṃvādī hoti evaṃdiṭṭhi: "
msgstr "It’s when someone has this doctrine and view: "

msgctxt "an3.156-162:1.6"
msgid "‘natthi kāmesu doso’ti. "
msgstr "‘There’s nothing wrong with sensual pleasures’; "

msgctxt "an3.156-162:1.7"
msgid "So kāmesu pātabyataṃ āpajjati. "
msgstr "so they throw themselves into sensual pleasures. "

msgctxt "an3.156-162:1.8"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, āgāḷhā paṭipadā. "
msgstr "This is called the addicted practice. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an3.156-162:2.1"
msgid "Katamā ca, bhikkhave, nijjhāmā paṭipadā? "
msgstr "And what’s the scorching practice? "

#. VAR: hatthāpalekhano → hatthāvalekhano (s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an3.156-162:2.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco acelako hoti muttācāro, hatthāpalekhano, naehibhadantiko, natiṭṭhabhadantiko, nābhihaṭaṃ na uddissakataṃ na nimantanaṃ sādiyati. "
msgstr "It’s when someone goes naked, ignoring conventions. They lick their hands, and don’t come or wait when asked. They don’t consent to food brought to them, or food prepared on purpose for them, or an invitation for a meal. "

# NOTE: https://discourse.suttacentral.net/t/on-the-austerities/3837
#. VAR: kaḷopimukhā → khaḷopimukhā (bj)
msgctxt "an3.156-162:2.3"
msgid "So na kumbhimukhā paṭiggaṇhāti, na kaḷopimukhā paṭiggaṇhāti na eḷakamantaraṃ na daṇḍamantaraṃ na musalamantaraṃ na dvinnaṃ bhuñjamānānaṃ na gabbhiniyā na pāyamānāya na purisantaragatāya na saṅkittīsu na yattha sā upaṭṭhito hoti na yattha makkhikā saṇḍasaṇḍacārinī na macchaṃ na maṃsaṃ na suraṃ na merayaṃ, na thusodakaṃ pivati. "
msgstr "They don’t receive anything from a pot or bowl; or from someone who keeps sheep, or who has a weapon or a shovel in their home; or where a couple is eating; or where there is a woman who is pregnant, breastfeeding, or who has a man in her home; or where there’s a dog waiting or flies buzzing. They accept no fish or meat or liquor or wine, and drink no beer. "

msgctxt "an3.156-162:2.4"
msgid "So ekāgāriko vā hoti ekālopiko, dvāgāriko vā hoti dvālopiko … sattāgāriko vā hoti sattālopiko; "
msgstr "They go to just one house for alms, taking just one mouthful, or two houses and two mouthfuls, up to seven houses and seven mouthfuls. "

msgctxt "an3.156-162:2.5"
msgid "ekissāpi dattiyā yāpeti, dvīhipi dattīhi yāpeti … sattahipi dattīhi yāpeti; "
msgstr "They feed on one saucer a day, two saucers a day, up to seven saucers a day. "

msgctxt "an3.156-162:2.6"
msgid "ekāhikampi āhāraṃ āhāreti, dvāhikampi āhāraṃ āhāreti … sattāhikampi āhāraṃ āhāreti—iti evarūpaṃ addhamāsikampi pariyāyabhattabhojanānuyogamanuyutto viharati. "
msgstr "They eat once a day, once every second day, up to once a week, and so on, even up to once a fortnight. They live pursuing the practice of eating food at set intervals. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an3.156-162:3.1"
msgid "So sākabhakkhopi hoti, sāmākabhakkhopi hoti, nīvārabhakkhopi hoti, daddulabhakkhopi hoti, haṭabhakkhopi hoti, kaṇabhakkhopi hoti, ācāmabhakkhopi hoti, piññākabhakkhopi hoti, tiṇabhakkhopi hoti, gomayabhakkhopi hoti, vanamūlaphalāhāro yāpeti pavattaphalabhojī. "
msgstr "They eat herbs, millet, wild rice, poor rice, water lettuce, rice bran, scum from boiling rice, sesame flour, grass, or cow dung. They survive on forest roots and fruits, or eating fallen fruit. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.296, sc4
msgctxt "an3.156-162:4.1"
msgid "So sāṇānipi dhāreti, masāṇānipi dhāreti, chavadussānipi dhāreti, paṃsukūlānipi dhāreti, tirīṭānipi dhāreti, ajinampi dhāreti, ajinakkhipampi dhāreti, kusacīrampi dhāreti, vākacīrampi dhāreti, phalakacīrampi dhāreti, kesakambalampi dhāreti, vāḷakambalampi dhāreti, ulūkapakkhikampi dhāreti, "
msgstr "They wear robes of sunn hemp, mixed hemp, corpse-wrapping cloth, rags, lodh tree bark, antelope hide (whole or in strips), kusa grass, bark, wood-chips, human hair, horse-tail hair, or owls’ wings. "

msgctxt "an3.156-162:4.2"
msgid "kesamassulocakopi hoti kesamassulocanānuyogamanuyutto, "
msgstr "They tear out their hair and beard, committed to this practice. "

msgctxt "an3.156-162:4.3"
msgid "ubbhaṭṭhakopi hoti āsanapaṭikkhitto, "
msgstr "They constantly stand, refusing seats. "

msgctxt "an3.156-162:4.4"
msgid "ukkuṭikopi hoti ukkuṭikappadhānamanuyutto, "
msgstr "They squat, committed to persisting in the squatting position. "

msgctxt "an3.156-162:4.5"
msgid "kaṇṭakāpassayikopi hoti kaṇṭakāpassaye seyyaṃ kappeti, "
msgstr "They lie on a mat of thorns, making a mat of thorns their bed. "

msgctxt "an3.156-162:4.6"
msgid "sāyatatiyakampi udakorohanānuyogamanuyutto viharati—"
msgstr "They pursue the practice of immersion in water three times a day, including the evening. "

msgctxt "an3.156-162:4.7"
msgid "iti evarūpaṃ anekavihitaṃ kāyassa ātāpanaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto viharati. "
msgstr "And so they live pursuing these various ways of mortifying and tormenting the body. "

msgctxt "an3.156-162:4.8"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, nijjhāmā paṭipadā. "
msgstr "This is called the scorching practice. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an3.156-162:5.1"
msgid "Katamā ca, bhikkhave, majjhimā paṭipadā? "
msgstr "And what’s the middle practice? "

msgctxt "an3.156-162:5.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ; "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the body—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world. "

msgctxt "an3.156-162:5.3"
msgid "vedanāsu … pe … "
msgstr "They meditate observing an aspect of feelings … "

msgctxt "an3.156-162:5.4"
msgid "citte … pe … "
msgstr "They meditate observing an aspect of the mind … "

msgctxt "an3.156-162:5.5"
msgid "dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ. "
msgstr "They meditate observing an aspect of principles—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world. "

msgctxt "an3.156-162:5.6"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, majjhimā paṭipadā. "
msgstr "This is called the middle practice. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.156-162:5.7"
msgid "Imā kho, bhikkhave, tisso paṭipadāti. (1) "
msgstr "These are the three practices. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "an3.156-162:6.1"
msgid "Tisso imā, bhikkhave, paṭipadā. "
msgstr "Mendicants, there are three practices. "

msgctxt "an3.156-162:6.2"
msgid "Katamā tisso? "
msgstr "What three? "

msgctxt "an3.156-162:6.3"
msgid "Āgāḷhā paṭipadā, nijjhāmā paṭipadā, majjhimā paṭipadā. "
msgstr "The addicted practice, the scorching practice, the middle practice. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.156-162:6.4"
msgid "Katamā ca, bhikkhave, āgāḷhā paṭipadā … pe … "
msgstr "And what’s the addicted practice? … "

msgctxt "an3.156-162:6.5"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, āgāḷhā paṭipadā. "
msgstr "This is called the addicted practice. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "an3.156-162:7.1"
msgid "Katamā ca, bhikkhave, nijjhāmā paṭipadā … pe … "
msgstr "And what is the scorching practice? … "

msgctxt "an3.156-162:7.2"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, nijjhāmā paṭipadā. "
msgstr "This is called the scorching practice. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.297, sc8
msgctxt "an3.156-162:8.1"
msgid "Katamā ca, bhikkhave, majjhimā paṭipadā? "
msgstr "And what’s the middle practice? "

msgctxt "an3.156-162:8.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu anuppannānaṃ pāpakānaṃ akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ anuppādāya chandaṃ janeti vāyamati vīriyaṃ ārabhati cittaṃ paggaṇhāti padahati; "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant generates enthusiasm, tries, makes an effort, exerts the mind, and strives so that bad, unskillful qualities don’t arise. "

msgctxt "an3.156-162:8.3"
msgid "uppannānaṃ pāpakānaṃ akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānāya chandaṃ janeti vāyamati vīriyaṃ ārabhati cittaṃ paggaṇhāti padahati; "
msgstr "They generate enthusiasm, try, make an effort, exert the mind, and strive so that bad, unskillful qualities that have arisen are given up. "

msgctxt "an3.156-162:8.4"
msgid "anuppannānaṃ kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ uppādāya chandaṃ janeti vāyamati vīriyaṃ ārabhati cittaṃ paggaṇhāti padahati; "
msgstr "They generate enthusiasm, try, make an effort, exert the mind, and strive so that skillful qualities arise. "

msgctxt "an3.156-162:8.5"
msgid "uppannānaṃ kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ ṭhitiyā asammosāya bhiyyobhāvāya vepullāya bhāvanāya pāripūriyā chandaṃ janeti vāyamati vīriyaṃ ārabhati cittaṃ paggaṇhāti padahati …. (2) "
msgstr "They generate enthusiasm, try, make an effort, exert the mind, and strive so that skillful qualities that have arisen remain, are not lost, but increase, mature, and are completed by development. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "an3.156-162:9.1"
msgid "Chandasamādhipadhānasaṅkhārasamannāgataṃ iddhipādaṃ bhāveti vīriyasamādhi … pe … "
msgstr "They develop the basis of psychic power that has immersion due to enthusiasm, and active effort. They develop the basis of psychic power that has immersion due to energy, and active effort. "

msgctxt "an3.156-162:9.2"
msgid "cittasamādhi … pe … "
msgstr "They develop the basis of psychic power that has immersion due to mental development, and active effort. "

msgctxt "an3.156-162:9.3"
msgid "vīmaṃsāsamādhipadhānasaṅkhārasamannāgataṃ iddhipādaṃ bhāveti … pe …. (3) "
msgstr "They develop the basis of psychic power that has immersion due to inquiry, and active effort. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "an3.156-162:10.1"
msgid "Saddhindriyaṃ bhāveti … "
msgstr "They develop the faculty of faith … "

msgctxt "an3.156-162:10.2"
msgid "vīriyindriyaṃ bhāveti … "
msgstr "energy … "

msgctxt "an3.156-162:10.3"
msgid "satindriyaṃ bhāveti … "
msgstr "mindfulness … "

msgctxt "an3.156-162:10.4"
msgid "samādhindriyaṃ bhāveti … "
msgstr "immersion … "

msgctxt "an3.156-162:10.5"
msgid "paññindriyaṃ bhāveti … pe …. (4) "
msgstr "wisdom … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc11
msgctxt "an3.156-162:11.1"
msgid "Saddhābalaṃ bhāveti … "
msgstr "They develop the power of faith … "

msgctxt "an3.156-162:11.2"
msgid "vīriyabalaṃ bhāveti … "
msgstr "energy … "

msgctxt "an3.156-162:11.3"
msgid "satibalaṃ bhāveti … "
msgstr "mindfulness … "

msgctxt "an3.156-162:11.4"
msgid "samādhibalaṃ bhāveti … "
msgstr "immersion … "

msgctxt "an3.156-162:11.5"
msgid "paññābalaṃ bhāveti … pe …. (5) "
msgstr "wisdom … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12
msgctxt "an3.156-162:12.1"
msgid "Satisambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāveti … "
msgstr "They develop the awakening factor of mindfulness … "

msgctxt "an3.156-162:12.2"
msgid "dhammavicayasambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāveti … "
msgstr "investigation of principles … "

msgctxt "an3.156-162:12.3"
msgid "vīriyasambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāveti … "
msgstr "energy … "

msgctxt "an3.156-162:12.4"
msgid "pītisambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāveti … "
msgstr "rapture … "

msgctxt "an3.156-162:12.5"
msgid "passaddhisambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāveti … "
msgstr "tranquility … "

msgctxt "an3.156-162:12.6"
msgid "samādhisambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāveti … "
msgstr "immersion … "

msgctxt "an3.156-162:12.7"
msgid "upekkhāsambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāveti … pe …. (6) "
msgstr "equanimity … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc13
msgctxt "an3.156-162:13.1"
msgid "Sammādiṭṭhiṃ bhāveti … "
msgstr "They develop right view … "

msgctxt "an3.156-162:13.2"
msgid "sammāsaṅkappaṃ bhāveti … "
msgstr "right thought … "

msgctxt "an3.156-162:13.3"
msgid "sammāvācaṃ bhāveti … "
msgstr "right speech … "

msgctxt "an3.156-162:13.4"
msgid "sammākammantaṃ bhāveti … "
msgstr "right action … "

msgctxt "an3.156-162:13.5"
msgid "sammāājīvaṃ bhāveti … "
msgstr "right livelihood … "

msgctxt "an3.156-162:13.6"
msgid "sammāvāyāmaṃ bhāveti … "
msgstr "right effort … "

msgctxt "an3.156-162:13.7"
msgid "sammāsatiṃ bhāveti … "
msgstr "right mindfulness … "

msgctxt "an3.156-162:13.8"
msgid "sammāsamādhiṃ bhāveti …. "
msgstr "right immersion … "

msgctxt "an3.156-162:13.9"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, majjhimā paṭipadā. "
msgstr "This is called the middle practice. "

msgctxt "an3.156-162:13.10"
msgid "Imā kho, bhikkhave, tisso paṭipadā”ti. (7) "
msgstr "These are the three practices.” "

